LEGOform
Brick by brick, module by module

Goal

Refactor a static configuration into a production-grade, modular system that integrates local logic with community-built modules from the Terraform Registry.

Instructions

The Local Module: Create a local module in ./modules/storage_account. This module should deploy an Azure Storage Account with variables for account_name, location, and account_tier.

The Registry Integration: In your root main.tf, use the official Azure Verified VNet Module from the Terraform Registry to deploy a Virtual Network.

The Factory: In your root main.tf, call your local storage module twice—once for a "Logging" account and once for a "Data" account.

The Export: Define an output in your root main.tf that displays the resource_id (from the Registry module) and the primary_blob_endpoint for both storage accounts (from your local module).

The Environments: Create a configs folder with dev.tfvars (Standard tier) and prod.tfvars (Premium tier).

The Test: Deploy the "dev" configuration using the var-file flag.

