Step 6: Deploy the Dev Environment
Now deploy using the dev configuration file. The -var-file flag tells Terraform which values to use:

terraform apply -var-file=configs/dev.tfvars
Terraform will show you a plan of what it will create:

Terraform will perform the following actions:

  # azurerm_resource_group.rg will be created
  # module.vnet.azurerm_virtual_network.this will be created
  # module.vnet.azurerm_subnet.this["default"] will be created
  # module.logging_storage.azurerm_storage_account.storage will be created
  # module.data_storage.azurerm_storage_account.storage will be created

Plan: 5 to add, 0 to change, 0 to destroy.
What you see:

1 resource group (created directly in root main.tf)

1 virtual network + 1 subnet (created by the Registry module)

2 storage accounts (created by your local module, called twice)

Type yes to confirm and create the resources.

