What You Learned
In this exercise, you learned these key concepts:

1. Local Modules
Reusable code stored in your project. Referenced by path:

module "my_module" {
  source = "./modules/storage_account"
}
2. Registry Modules
Pre-built modules from the Terraform Registry. We use Azure Verified Modules (AVM) - the official modules maintained by Microsoft:

module "vnet" {
  source  = "Azure/avm-res-network-virtualnetwork/azurerm"
  version = "0.17.0"  # Always pin versions!
}
3. Module Inputs and Outputs
Inputs (variables.tf): Parameters you pass TO the module

Outputs (outputs.tf): Values you get BACK from the module

Access outputs with: module.<name>.<output>

4. The Factory Pattern
Call the same module multiple times with different parameters. Each call creates independent resources.

5. Environment Configuration
Use different .tfvars files for different environments. Apply with -var-file flag.

